workflow.name: Automate high-value lead alerts from GoHighLevel to Slack, Sheets and Calendar
workflow.description:
## üìä Description
Streamline sales prioritization by automatically identifying, scoring, and routing high-value leads from GoHighLevel CRM to your sales team. This workflow scores contacts daily, flags top prospects, alerts sales reps in Slack, logs data to Google Sheets, and schedules instant follow-ups in Google Calendar ‚Äî ensuring no valuable lead slips through the cracks. üöÄüìà

## What This Template Does
- Triggers daily at 8:00 AM to fetch all contacts from GoHighLevel CRM. ‚è∞
- Processes lead data and extracts key details from custom fields. üß©
- Calculates lead scores using your predefined CRM field mappings. üî¢
- Filters out incomplete or invalid contacts to ensure clean data flow. üßº
- Identifies high-value leads with a score above 80 for immediate attention. üéØ
- Sends real-time Slack alerts to sales teams with contact and lead score details. üí¨
- Logs high-priority leads into a dedicated Google Sheet for tracking and analytics. üìä
- Creates automatic Google Calendar follow-up events within 1 hour of detection. üìÖ

## Key Benefits
‚úÖ Automatically surfaces top leads for faster follow-up
 ‚úÖ Keeps sales teams aligned through instant Slack alerts
 ‚úÖ Eliminates manual data review and prioritization
 ‚úÖ Centralizes performance tracking via Google Sheets
 ‚úÖ Ensures consistent follow-up with Google Calendar scheduling
 ‚úÖ Fully customizable lead score threshold and timing

## Features
- Daily scheduled trigger (8:00 AM)
- GoHighLevel CRM integration for contact retrieval
- Smart lead scoring via custom field mapping
- Conditional filtering for high-value leads
- Slack alert system for real-time engagement
- Google Sheets logging for transparency and analytics
- Auto-created Google Calendar events for follow-ups

## Requirements
- GoHighLevel API credentials with contact read permissions
- Slack Bot token with chat:write access
- Google Sheets OAuth2 credentials
- Google Calendar OAuth2 credentials
- Defined custom fields for Lead Score and Assigned Representative in GoHighLevel

## Target Audience
- Sales and business development teams tracking high-value leads
- Marketing teams optimizing lead qualification and follow-up
- Agencies using GoHighLevel for CRM and lead management
- Operations teams centralizing sales activity and analytics

## Step-by-Step Setup Instructions
- Connect your GoHighLevel OAuth2 credentials and ensure contact API access.
- Replace placeholder custom field IDs (Lead Score & Assigned Rep) in the Code node.
- Add your Slack channel ID for team notifications.
- Connect your Google Sheets document and replace its Sheet ID in the workflow.
- Link Google Calendar for automatic follow-up event creation.
- Adjust the lead score threshold (default: 80) if needed.
- Run a manual test to verify data flow, then enable the daily trigger for automation.

workflow.name: Automate High-Value Lead Alerts from GoHighLevel to Slack ,Sheets and Calender

parameters.content:
## üéØ High-Value Lead Scoring & Alert System

This workflow automatically:
- Fetches contacts from HighLevel CRM daily at 8 AM
- Calculates lead scores from custom fields
- Alerts sales team via Slack for leads scoring >80
- Logs high-priority leads to Google Sheets
- Creates follow-up calendar events automatically

**Setup Required:**
1. Connect HighLevel OAuth2 credentials
2. Connect Slack API credentials
3. Connect Google Sheets OAuth2
4. Connect Google Calendar OAuth2
5. Update Slack channel ID with your channel
6. Update Google Sheet ID with your tracking sheet
7. Map custom field IDs to match your CRM setup

## ‚è∞ Daily Trigger

Runs every day at 8:00 AM to check for new high-value leads.

**Customization:**
Adjust the trigger time in node settings to match your team's schedule.

## üì• Fetch All Contacts

**Before Using:**
1. Connect your HighLevel OAuth2 credentials
2. Ensure API access is enabled in your HighLevel account
3. Test with a small batch first

**Note:** This retrieves ALL contacts. Consider adding filters if you have a large database.

## üîç Filter Contacts with Custom Fields

Only processes contacts that have custom fields populated.

This prevents errors when trying to extract lead scores from incomplete data.

## ‚öôÔ∏è Transform Contact Data

**Custom Field IDs to Update:**
- Lead Score Field: `sEic9OWa5yndTAitjgoe`
- Assigned Rep Field: `YHJqNOSAvMbI08mnabNb`

**Action Required:**
Replace these IDs with YOUR actual custom field IDs from HighLevel.

Find them in: HighLevel ‚Üí Settings ‚Üí Custom Fields ‚Üí Copy Field ID

## üéØ Lead Score Filter

Only leads with score **>80** proceed to alerting.

**Customization:**
Adjust the threshold (currently 80) to match your lead qualification criteria.

## üö® Slack Alert Setup

**Required Configuration:**
1. Create a Slack App with chat:write permissions
2. Install app to your workspace
3. Get your channel ID:
   - Right-click channel ‚Üí View channel details ‚Üí Copy ID
4. Replace `YOUR_SLACK_CHANNEL_ID` in node settings

**Security:** Never commit channel IDs to public repositories.

## üìä Google Sheets Logging

**Setup Steps:**
1. Create a Google Sheet with these columns:
   contact_id, contact_name, first_name, last_name, email, phone, company_name, lead_score, assigned_rep, assigned_rep_slack_id, location_id, source, tags, country, date_added, date_updated, is_high_priority

2. Share sheet with your service account email
3. Copy the Sheet ID from URL
4. Replace `YOUR_GOOGLE_SHEET_ID` in node settings

**Security:** Use environment variables for Sheet IDs in production.

## üìÖ Auto-Schedule Follow-up

Creates a calendar event 1 hour from now for immediate follow-up.

**Configuration:**
1. Connect Google Calendar OAuth2
2. Replace `YOUR_CALENDAR_EMAIL` with your team calendar
3. Adjust timing: Currently set to 1-1.5 hours from trigger

**Tip:** Use a shared team calendar for better visibility.

data.details:
The IF node can be used to implement binary conditional logic in your workflow. You can set up one-to-many conditions to evaluate each item of data being inputted into the node. That data will either evaluate to TRUE or FALSE and route out of the node accordingly.

This node has multiple types of conditions: Bool, String, Number, and Date & Time.
